articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China will require export permits for some graphite products from Dec. 1 to protect national security, the commerce ministry said on Friday, in the latest move to control supplies of critical raw materials.
articles.title: China to require export permits on some graphite products from Dec 1

articles.author: Saqib Ahmed
articles.description: Relentless selling of U.S. government bonds has brought Treasury yields to their highest level in more than a decade and a half, roiling everything from stocks to the real estate market.
articles.title: Falling stocks, climbing mortgage rates: how 5% Treasury yields could roil markets

articles.author: Josh Ye
articles.description: While Nvidia (NVDA.O) has historically been the leading provider of AI chips in China with a market share exceeding 90%, Chinese firms including Huawei have been developing their own versions of Nvidia’s best-selling chips, including the A100 and the H100 graphics processing units (GPU).
articles.title: Analysis: US chip curbs give Huawei a chance to fill the Nvidia void in China

articles.author: Rodrigo Campos
articles.description: Argentines will on Sunday move a step closer to deciding who will run the $600 billion economy engulfed by a deep crisis that involves runaway inflation, a dearth of U.S. dollar reserves and an electorate with little trust in its currency.
articles.title: Analysis: Dollarization, devaluation, debt: potential traps for Argentina investors

articles.author: Clare Jim, Liangping Gao
articles.description: China's troubled property market is showing little signs of a recovery in the short term despite a series of government stimulus measures to help revive activity in the sector which makes up a quarter of the nation's economic output.
articles.title: China property market shows little signs of revival despite stimulus

articles.author: Huw Jones, Simon Jessop
articles.description: Britain needs to better track funds going into green investments to assess how much is needed from the private sector and should consider targeted tax changes to encourage sustainable projects, banking industry body UK Finance said.
articles.title: Banks call for clarity on Britain's investment path to net-zero economy

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Elon Musk said on Friday social media platform X, formerly known as Twitter, will soon launch two new tiers of premium subscriptions.
articles.title: Elon Musk's X to launch premium subscriptions soon

articles.author: Steve Holland, Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Emily Rose
articles.description: President Joe Biden on Thursday asked Americans to spend billions more dollars to help Israel fight Hamas while Israel's defence chief told his troops to be ready to go into the Gaza Strip to destroy the Palestinian militant group.
articles.title: Biden to seek billions in military aid for Israel as invasion of Gaza nears

articles.author: Steve Holland, Jarrett Renshaw, Patricia Zengerle
articles.description: President Joe Biden launched a new mission on Thursday to convince Americans they should spend billions more on supporting Israel and Ukraine in their wars, arguing that only the U.S.'s involvement can prevent global chaos.
articles.title: US leadership 'holds the world together,' Biden says in bid for Ukraine, Israel funds

articles.author: Andrew Macaskill, Elizabeth Piper
articles.description: Britain's Labour Party dealt a crushing blow to Prime Minister Rishi Sunak's Conservatives on Friday, winning two previously safe parliamentary seats in victories leader Keir Starmer said showed voters wanted change at the next national election.
articles.title: Britain's Labour deals big by-election blows to PM Sunak
